{"serial": "48030", "department_serial": 40, "code": "FM6094", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Market Microstructure", "ch": "市場微結構"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "不在分發優先順序內或名額外學生請拿密碼卡。"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Lai, Hung-Neng"], "ch": ["賴弘能"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "I", "room": "402"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 40, "department": {"ch": "財務金融學系", "en": "Department of Finance"}, "system": {"ch": "碩士班", "en": "Master Programs"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 44, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "不在分發優先順序內或名額外學生請拿密碼卡。", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "市場價格是由眾多投資人及中介人互動所決定。當投資人決定買賣標的後，通常希望以成本低，速度快，而且較不為人知的方式達成交易。本課程將介紹各種交易方式，從投資人的角度探討下單策略，從金融中介機構的角度探討交易機制設計，從主管機關的角度探討交易的管理。", "en": "“Prices are determined through the interactions among investors and intermediaries.  After the investors decide to trade certain assets, they would like to do so inexpensively, swiftly, and stealthily.   This course will introduce trading methods and will discuss trading strategies from investors’ points of view, trading mechanism design from intermediaries’ points of view, and trading regulations from the regulator’s point of view.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "本課程原則上兩年開一次，預計下次開課時間為113學年度下學期。\n由於校方對大學部課程的限制較多， 例如修課人數最少十五人，碩士班選修大學部不予承認等等， 所以本課程列為碩士班課程。 適合選修本課程的同學包括財金系碩士班，大學部修過財金系投資學(FM3017 FM3041)，以及管院其他各系所碩士班曾選修過投資學的同學。", "en": "由於校方對大學部課程的限制較多， 例如修課人數最少十五人，碩士班選修大學部不予承認等等， 所以本課程列為碩士班課程。 適合選修本課程的同學包括財金系碩士班，大學部修過財金系投資學(FM3017 FM3041)，以及管院其他各系所碩士班曾選修過投資學的同學。"}, "textbook": {"ch": "1 Harris, Larry, 2015, Trading and Electronic Markets: What Investment Professionals Need to Know, CFA Institute, available at http://ssrn.com/abstract=2692539    2. Foucault, Thierry, Marco Pagano, and Ailsa R?ell, 2013, Market Liquidity: Theory, Evidence, and Policy, Oxford University Press.", "en": "1 Harris, Larry, 2015, Trading and Electronic Markets: What Inve